    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1959-08-31T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1959-08-31T15:00:00-05:00" n="357"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d357">
                <head>357. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Embassy in Cuba</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d357fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 837.2614/8–3159. Confidential; Priority.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Havana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1959-08-31T15:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 31, 1959—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>530. In course brief interview this morning <persName corresp="#p_RR1"
                        >Roa</persName> told me <persName corresp="#p_CRF1">Castro</persName> would
                    see me probably this week. I was unable to tell <persName corresp="#p_RR1"
                        >Roa</persName> and his two young sub-secretaries of our reaction to
                    treatment electric company (<gloss target="#t_DEPTEL1">Deptel</gloss> 268<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d357fn2">Not printed. (<hi rend="italic">ibid</hi>.,
                        837.2614/8–2059)</note>). Am seeing <persName corresp="#p_RR1"
                        >Roa</persName> again morning September 2 and would appreciate any further
                    suggestions from Department. I expect rehearse whole range our relations along
                    lines already set forth to Department and which I understand has Department’s
                    approval. <persName corresp="#p_RR1">Roa</persName> added that he hoped
                        <persName corresp="#p_DE1">Dihigo</persName> would be returning here end of
                    week to participate in talks. I said I hoped to go to Washington about 14th.
                        <persName corresp="#p_RR1">Roa</persName> mentioned possibility including
                        <persName corresp="#p_BLR1">Boti</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_PF1"
                        >Pazos</persName> in conversations. I shall explore this further.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BPW1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Bonsal</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
